{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Meatballs","content":["Place bread into mixing bowl and grate <b>5 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place onion, parsley and dried herbs into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add olive oil and sauté <b>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","Add rump steak and chop <b>15 sec\/speed 8<b>, or until an evenly-chopped chunky consistency is achieved.","Add egg, milk, salt, pepper and reserved breadcrumbs and combine <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Form the mince mixture into approx. 20 small meatballs. Place a non-stick frying pan over medium heat and add oil. Cook meatballs until browned all over and cooked through (approx. 4-5 minutes). You may need to cook meatballs in 2 batches.","Transfer meatballs into a large bowl and set aside to keep warm. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"White wine mushroom sauce","content":["Place Parmesan into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl, then weigh white wine into it. Add corn starch to bowl and combine until corn starch has dissolved.","Place garlic and shallot into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>, or until a finely chopped consistency is achieved. Repeat if necessary. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter and sauté <b>2 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","Add mushrooms and cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid.","Add reserved cornstarch paste and cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid","Add salt, pepper, cream and reserved Parmesan and cook <b>4 min\/90°C\/\/speed <b>, or until sauce is heated and warm, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid","Serve meatballs with mushroom sauce and garnish with flat-leaf parsley before serving (see tip)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Meatballs","content":["80 g stale white bread","½ onion","4 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","1 tsp mixed herbs, dried","20 g olive oil","500 g beef rump steak, trimmed, cut into pieces (4 cm) and slightly frozen","1 egg","20 g milk","½ tsp fine salt","½ tsp freshly ground black pepper"]},{"title":"White wine mushroom sauce","content":["60 g Parmesan cheese, cut into pieces (3 cm)","60 g dry white wine","1 tbsp cornflour (starch)","1 garlic clove","1 shallot (approx. 30 g)","40 g butter","200 g button mushrooms, fresh, cut into thin slices","1 pinch fine salt, to taste","1 pinch freshly ground black pepper, to taste","200 g cream","1 sprig fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r131696","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-HlOFV8YTl40\/XZQHaLGjVNI\/AAAAAAAAcIA\/Zjd0_69bBUQ2bwZvhTxFIhOKXqMrWfAvgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_iXyVti17BVYlBSPG.png","title":"Meatballs with white wine mushroom sauce","publishedAt":"2017-08-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"36.2 g","fat":"39.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"9 g","calories":"2238 kJ \/ 532 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, ceramic or glass bowl, bowl, non-stick frying pan, stove","hintsAndTricks":["Meatballs in mushroom sauce are delicious served with fresh crusty bread and a green salad."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","35m","6 portions"]}